o  hired on or after  hired on or after  as a new calpers member poff mpp public safety  at  one year highest compensation highest benefit factor  at age   at   month average compensation highest benefit factor  at age   at  consecutive  month subject to cap highest benefit factor  at age  state safety limited to intermittent peace officer  at  one year of highest compensation highest benefit factor  at age   at   month average compensation highest benefit factor  at age   at  consecutive  month subject to cap highest benefit factor  at age    hired prior to   hired on or after   hired on or after  as a new calpers member poff unit     one year highest compensation highest benefit factor  at age   at   month average compensation highest benefit factor  at age   at  consecutive  month subject to cap highest benefit factor  at age  please note employees who became members of calpers on or after  are subject to the irc a  limit which restricts the amount of compensation that can be used to calculate the calpers retirement benefit for  the limit is  employees who become new members of calpers on or after  are subject to a compensation cap of  if participating in social security or  if not participating in social security such as public safety employees these amounts represent the maximum salary that can count toward final compensation and calculation of retirement benefits for employees that are placed in the  at   at  or  at  retirement formulas in addition once an employees salary reaches the compensation cap during the year the employees retirement contributions will be stopped and restarted in january of the following year calpers retirement contributions employees contribute a percentage of gross monthly income minus the applicable offset amount gross income  offset amount x applicable  employees in retirement formulas  at  and  at  and  at  are not subject to the offset amount the contribution is not subject to federal and state taxes the csu also contributes to calpers calpers retirement benefits the plan is a defined benefit plan with retirement benefits calculated based on age at retirement years of service and compensation plan vesting is at five years of pers credited service members in the  at  and  at  benefit formulas have a minimum retirement age of  members in the  at  benefit formula are eligible to retire at the minimum age of fiftytwo  employees are eligible to retire and receive a monthly pension when they are at the minimum retirement age and have five years of calperscredited service any unused sick leave is converted to additional service credit if the employee retires within  days of separation from employment eight hours of sick leave equals one day  of a year of service it takes  days of sick leave to receive one year of service credit  x    year calpers may require up to  months after the retirement date to calculate sick leave once completed your adjusted pension will be retroactive to the date of retirementcsu retiree medical dental and vision benefits are available to eligible employees and their eligible dependents who retire within  days from the date of separation from employment applying for calpers service retirement employees should begin their retirement planning at least one year before their retirement date however they should not submit their application to calpers sooner than  days prior to their retirement date completed applications should be mailed to the calpers address at the bottom of page  of the application application resources regional offices calpers power of attorney the calpers special power of attorney allows the member to designate a representative or agent to conduct their retirement affairs if they are unable to act on their own behalf calpers beneficiary designation the calpers beneficiary designation form allows the member to designate primary and secondary beneficiaries for payment of specific death benefits in the event the member dies before retirement social security as a member of calpers employees also participate in social security social security and medicare taxes are withheld from your paycheck  withholding rates are  percent for social security and  percent for medicare social security resources social security faq this official site includes questions and answers about social security benefits social security administration ssa website other retirement resources calpers state member benefits brochures calpers official retirement website note documents in portable document format pdf require adobe acrobat reader  or higher to view download adobe acrobat reader print this page maps  directions contact us register a complaint career opportunities copyright  california state university east bay all rights reserved •  carlos bee boulevard hayward ca  • phone  benefits skip to navigation skip to content skip to search skip to quicklinks about csueb academic programs library athletics news calendar people finder az directory search our site human resourcespayrollprospective studentscurrent studentsfacultystaffalumni  friends quicklinks blackboard career opportunities campus directory campus safety report class schedule college and departments csueb online university scheduling horizon student email mycsueb university catalog university calendar it knowledge base apply online giving to csueb benefitsemployee medical plansmedical plansdental plansvision planflex cashcobratax shelter annuity program b k csu east bay tax shelter annuity representativesvoluntary pretax programslife insuranceemployerpaid life and accidental death  dismemberment insurancevoluntary life insuranceretirement programscalifornia public employees retirement systemparttime seasonal temporary pstmiscellaneous benefit programsaflac critical illness planauto insurance  home loanscalpers longterm carecredit unionsemployee assistance program eapemployee discount opportunitieshellowalletmetlife legal planus saving bondsscholarshareleave programsbereavement and fun