california via the state controller’s office will issue a form c to its fulltime employees with information about the health coverage offered if any to the employee and their dependent children the state’s health coverage providers will also issue a form b to employees who were enrolled in statesponsored health coverage for at least one day during the preceding calendar year please review the frequently asked questions regarding these forms as well as a glossary of commonly used terms frequently asked questions faqs about irs b contact us office of human resources california state university east bay  carlos bee blvd sa  hayward ca      tty quick links open enrollment   health plan premium rates calpers chancellors office  benefits retirement tools affordable care act csu transition guide tsa print this page maps  directions contact us register a complaint career opportunities copyright  california state university east bay all rights reserved •  carlos bee boulevard hayward ca  • phone  retirement programs skip to navigation skip to content skip to search skip to quicklinks about csueb academic programs library athletics news calendar people finder az directory human resourcespayrollprospective studentscurrent studentsfacultystaffalumni  friends quicklinks blackboard career opportunities campus directory campus safety report class schedule college and departments csueb online university scheduling horizon student email mycsueb university catalog university calendar it knowledge base apply online giving to csueb benefitsemployee medical plansmedical plansdental plansvision planflex cashcobratax shelter annuity program b k csu east bay tax shelter annuity representativesvoluntary pretax programslife insuranceemployerpaid life and accidental death  dismemberment insurancevoluntary life insuranceretirement programscalifornia public employees retirement systemparttime seasonal temporary pstmiscellaneous benefit programsaflac critical illness planauto insurance  home loa